com.hazelcast.web.entryprocessor

Class GetAttributeEntryProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.web.entryprocessor.GetAttributeEntryProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EntryProcessor<String,SessionState>, DataSerializable, IdentifiedDataSerializable, JvmIdAware, Serializable

    public final class GetAttributeEntryProcessor
extends Object
implements EntryProcessor<String,SessionState>, IdentifiedDataSerializable, JvmIdAware
    Entry processor which return attributes of SessionState values and adds current jvmId into SessionState. See GetAttributeEntryProcessor.process

      • process

        public Data process(Map.Entry<String,SessionState> entry)
        Description copied from interface: EntryProcessor
        Process the entry without worrying about concurrency.

        Note that to modify an entry by using EntryProcessor you should explicitly call Map.Entry.setValue(V) method of Map.Entry such as: 

         
 Override
        public Object process(Map.Entry entry) {
          Value value = entry.getValue();
          // process and modify value
          // ...
          entry.setValue(value);
          return result;
        }
        otherwise EntryProcessor does not guarantee to modify the entry.
        Specified by:
        process in interface EntryProcessor<String,SessionState>
        Parameters:
        entry - entry to be processed
        Returns:
        result of the process
